<subSubSection box="[199,1064,1721,1746]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,389,2034]" box="[199,1064,1721,1746]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1721,1745]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for its occurrence in 
<collectingRegion box="[817,1060,1721,1746]" country="Iran" name="Hormozgan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hormozgan Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,389,2034]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[199,315,1757,1781]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1757,1781]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Due to the similar general shape of the coxal field, palp and legs, as well the presence of long setae of D2 and D3, the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[561,606,1794,1817]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Iran</collectingCountry>
closely resemble 
<taxonomicName authority="Smit &amp; Pesic, 2010" authorityName="Smit &amp; Pesic" authorityYear="2010" box="[815,1268,1793,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiseta">
<emphasis box="[815,1033,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nilotonia longiseta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[1043,1268,1793,1817]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="151 - 195" refId="ref34331" refString="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V. (2010) New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Acarologia, 50 (2), 151 - 195." type="journal article" year="2010">Smit &amp; Pešić, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,1829,1853]" name="Oman" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[236,459,1829,1853]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="151 - 195" refId="ref34331" refString="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V. (2010) New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Acarologia, 50 (2), 151 - 195." type="journal article" year="2010">Smit &amp; Pešić 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The species from 
<collectingCountry box="[684,752,1829,1853]" name="Oman" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Oman</collectingCountry>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Saboori, 2012" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit &amp; Saboori" authorityYear="2012" box="[906,1160,1829,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hormozgana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[906,1160,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nilotonia hormozgana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1170,1260,1829,1853]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1170,1254,1829,1853]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in much larger dimensions of the dorsal plate (L/W 160 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[602,616,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">–</emphasis>
218/ 
<quantity box="[666,791,1865,1889]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3019999999999996" metricValueMax="3.7592" metricValueMin="2.8448" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="130.0" valueMax="148.0" valueMin="112.0">
112 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,721,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">–</emphasis>
148 in
</quantity>
male, 150 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[908,922,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">–</emphasis>
196/ 
<quantity box="[972,1099,1865,1889]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9718" metricValueMax="3.2512" metricValueMin="2.6924" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="117.0" valueMax="128.0" valueMin="106.0">
106 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1014,1028,1865,1889]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">–</emphasis>
128 in
</quantity>
female) and postgenital sclerite (L/W 106/ 
<quantity box="[307,380,1901,1925]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6416" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="in" value="104.0">104 in</quantity>
the 
<typeStatus box="[431,529,1901,1925]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
male) in both sexes, and in the shape of the female pregenital sclerite which is strongly extended anteriorly (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[525,741,1937,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="151 - 195" refId="ref34331" refString="Smit, H. &amp; Pesic, V. (2010) New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia). Acarologia, 50 (2), 151 - 195." type="journal article" year="2010">Smit &amp; Pešić 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,389,2034]" box="[199,1178,1973,1998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1973,1998]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Sandy/bouldery streams, often with strong exposure to sunlight (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1166,1973,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 44" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[179,1411,179,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-98@60.[179,1411,169,1840]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 44A–D. Running water habitats: A — saline stream near Khorgoo village (locus typicus of Haloaxonopsis salina); B — the shallow stream N of Bandar Abbass (locus typicus of Nilotonia hormozgana and Axonopsis gloeeri); C — stream in Banglayan village (locus typicus of Torrenticola asadiae, T. hormozganus, Monatractides martini and Neoatractides calidus); D — Rudan stream (locus typicus of Atractides hormozganus, Javalbia persica, Axonopsis interstitialis, A. hyporheica, and Albia hyporheica). Photos. V. Pešić." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 44B, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
